.TH "bitmap_parse_user" 9 "bitmap_parse_user" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bitmap_parse_user \- convert an ASCII hex string in a user buffer into a bitmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bitmap_parse_user
.BI "(const char __user *ubuf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ulen "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *maskp "  ","
.BI "int nmaskbits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ubuf" 12
pointer to user buffer containing string.
.IP "ulen" 12
buffer size in bytes.  If string is smaller than this
then it must be terminated with a \0.
.IP "maskp" 12
pointer to bitmap array that will contain result.
.IP "nmaskbits" 12
size of bitmap, in bits.
